organic_results.title: Models for educational and occupational achievement over time
organic_results.snippet: Following Sorensen (1974), this paper formulates two models for the process of occupational achievement over time. Unlike Sorensen, this paper considers models which explicitly include the effects of changes in education on changes in occupational achievement; that is, the models do not assume that resources are stable over the career.
